author: CNN
description: President Trump’s surprise plan to raise H-1B application fees to $100,000 sparked confusion among foreign workers and companies, prompting the White House to clarify it applies only to new applications. The administration says the fee aims to curb program abuse, but it could significantly impact US employers who rely on H-1B workers for hard-to-fill skilled roles.   #CNN #News
title: Medical recruiters warn H-1B visa changes could impact healthcare staffing

author: CNN
description: Roy Wood Jr. talks to his panel about Donald Trump’s latest run-in with an escalator. “Have I Got News For You” regularly airs Saturdays at 9pm ET/PT and streams on HBO Max the following day.
title: Comedians react to Trump’s latest ‘adversary’: An escalator

author: CNN
description: A Los Angeles business owner has filed a $50 million civil rights claim alleging federal immigration agents body slammed him to the ground during an immigration raid.
title: 79-year-old slammed to the ground during ICE raid

author: CNN
description: CNN’s Michael Smerconish comments on how political violence in America is less about left vs. right and more about a deeper crisis among young men - marked by isolation, mental health struggles and vulnerability to digital platforms that fuel anger.   #CNN #News
title: Analysis: The real threat behind US political violence

author: CNN
description:
A possible federal government shutdown is only days away as congressional lawmakers remain at odds over funding the government beyond September 30.

Although Republicans control Capitol Hill and the White House, they need at least seven Democrats in the Senate to join them to pass a spending package under the chamber’s rules.

CNN's Danny Freeman speaks with Max Cohen, Congressional reporter for Punchbowl News. #CNN #News
title: The US government could shut down Wednesday

author: CNN
description: The international aid group Doctors Without Borders says it is suspending its operations in Gaza City because of deteriorating conditions. CNN's Danny Freeman speaks with Dr. Aqsa Durrani, a pediatrician who serves on the MSF USA board. #CNN #News
title: Doctors Without Borders pulls its staff out of Gaza City

author: CNN
description:
The United States announced it would cancel the visa of Colombia’s President Gustavo Petro after he publicly called on its soldiers to disobey President Donald Trump, further straining relations between Washington and Bogota.

Petro repeated his call for an armed force to “free Palestine” while addressing a group of pro-Palestine supporters outside the United Nations headquarters on Friday.

CNN contributor Stefano Pozzebon reports from Bogota. #CNN #News
title: US revokes Colombian president's visa after Gaza protest speech

author: CNN
description: A tropical depression forming near the Bahamas is expected to intensify quickly, threatening the Southeast U.S. with flooding rains, storm surge, strong winds, and dangerous surf as early as Monday.   #CNN #News
title: Tropical storm watch in effect for parts of Florida’s East Coast

author: CNN
description:
President Donald Trump said in a social media post Saturday he is directing Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth to “provide all necessary troops” to Portland, Oregon, a city he described as “war ravaged,” to protect Immigration and Customs Enforcement facilities he claimed are “under siege” by Antifa and “other domestic terrorists.”

CNN senior White House reporter Kevin Liptak reports from the White House. #CNN #News
title: Trump says he's sending troops to protect 'war ravaged Portland'

author: CNN
description:
President Donald Trump's granddaughter, Kai Trump, posted a series of photos and videos taken at the White House to promote sweatshirts she is selling on her website. The 18-year-old has millions of followers across social media.

#CNN #News #Trump #KaiTrump
title: Trump's granddaughter launched her new merch at the White House

author: CNN
description: CNN's Michael Smerconish speaks with Jeffrey Selingo, college admissions expert and author of "Dream School: Finding the College That's Right for You" and "Who Gets In and Why: A Year Inside College Admissions." #CNN #News
title: College admissions expert: 'We're just putting a tremendous amount of pressure on our kids'

author: CNN
description:
Sinclair and Nexstar, the two major station groups that preempted "Jimmy Kimmel Live!" earlier this month, have backed down, ending their boycott and allowing the show to return to their ABC-affiliated stations. The reversal is a victory for Kimmel and ABC and a reflection of the power that national networks have over local affiliates.

CNN's Veronica Miracle speaks with Eric Deggans, NPR TV & media critic. #CNN #News
title: Trump threatens to sue ABC over Kimmel's return

author: CNN
description:
Pregnant people should not be afraid to take Tylenol, experts say, rebuking unproven claims made by the Trump administration that it can cause autism. 

The FDA is reviewing evidence about the safety and efficacy of mifepristone, one of the drugs used in medication abortion, to investigate how it can be safely dispensed, according to a letter by HHS Secretary Robert F. Kennedy, Jr. and FDA Commissioner Dr. Marty Makary. Mifepristone was approved by the FDA in 2000.

CNN's Veronica Miracle speaks with Dr. Harry Heiman, professor in the School of Public Health at Georgia State University. #CNN #News
title: FDA studying safety of abortion drug mifepristone, spurring concerns about limits on access

author: CNN
description:
Secretary of Defense Pete Hegseth has shut down the Defense Advisory Committee on Women in the Services, which has been advising the Pentagon since 1951. The advisory group offered recommendations on how to support women serving in the military, including past suggestions that women needed properly fitting body armor and appropriate health care.

Pentagon Press Secretary Kingsley Wilson said in a post on X on Tuesday that Secretary Hegseth had decided to eliminate the group, formally called the Defense Advisory Committee on Women in the Services, saying that the committee, “focused on advancing a divisive feminist agenda that hurts combat readiness.” CNN's Veronica Miracle speaks with retired US Marine Corps Captain Angie Morgan. #CNN #News
title: Defense Secretary Hegseth shuts down group advising on women in the military

description: An ICE officer dropped his handgun during a struggle to make an arrest, a video from Wednesday shows. He appeared to then point it in the direction of bystanders. description: Kevin Hart, Dave Chappelle, and Bill Burr are among the list of comedians headlining Saudi Arabia’s new Riyadh Comedy Festival. Still, other comedians are slamming the performers for what they see as helping the Saudi government improve its image.
title: Comedians slam Saudi Arabia’s new comedy festival
